# Testing

## Pytest (Backend Unit Tests)
- Place tests in `backend/tests/` mirroring source structure
- Name files `test_<module>.py`; name functions `test_<behavior>()`
- Use `pytest.fixture` for reusable setup; prefer factory fixtures over large objects
- Use `httpx.AsyncClient` with `ASGITransport` for testing FastAPI endpoints
- Mock external services at the boundary; never mock SQLModel internals
- Aim for isolated tests: each test gets a clean DB transaction (rollback after)
- Run: `cd backend && uv run pytest -x -q`

## Playwright (Frontend E2E Tests)
- Place tests in `frontend/tests/` organized by feature
- Name files `<feature>.spec.ts`
- Use Page Object Model: one class per page/component in `tests/pages/`
- Prefer `getByRole`, `getByLabel`, `getByText` locators — avoid CSS selectors
- Always `await expect(...)` for assertions; no raw `waitForTimeout`
- Use `test.describe` to group related scenarios
- Run: `bun run test` from root or `frontend/`

## General
- Every new endpoint gets at least one happy-path + one error-path test
- Every new UI feature gets at least one e2e smoke test
- Tests must be deterministic; no sleeping, no reliance on external services
